The paper deals with applying convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to compressed images, which is a problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses compression algorithms, which falls under the category of multimedia (MM), making cs.MM another likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new technique called Localized Compression, which involves dividing the image into blocks and compressing each block, which is related to the field of machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the compatibility of the compression algorithm with CNN architectures, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of sampling and random-matrix-based techniques, which is related to information theory (IT), making cs.IT a possible sub-category.
